 Wow, they're earrings. 

26
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,040
 Happy birthday. 

27
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,580
 You should wear this to dinner tonight. 

28
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,300
 He's in my class. A dermatology intern. 

29
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:55,710
 I couldn't stand the sight of him all excited to have dinner with Joo Won tonight. 

30
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,710
 I had a bad feeling. 

31
00:01:57,710 --> 00:01:59,950
 He must've finally asked her out. 

32
00:02:03,170 --> 00:02:04,790
 Don't go. 

33
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:09,550
 Don't go, Yoon Joo Won. 

34
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,170
I like you.

35
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:27,170
It took me ten years to tell you that I like you.

36
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:30,800
So...

37
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:35,400
♫  Even though I'm right next to you  ♫

38
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,230
Don't go.

39
00:02:38,230 --> 00:02:42,710
♫  It’s like you’re on the other side of the earth  ♫

40
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:50,120
Sure. I like you, too, Oppa.

41
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,940
I like Dad, Ahjusshi, and Kang Hae Joon, too, you know.

42
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:55,000
I like you guys a lot.

43
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,160
Is it because I was mean to you yesterday?

44
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:00,010
That was just...

45
00:03:03,090 --> 00:03:05,440
That was...

46
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,630
just...

47
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:08,800
You're not oblivious.

48
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:12,120
You know what I'm trying to tell you.

49
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,320
I'll get going.

50
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:22,090
♫  My one promise for the rest of my life  ♫

51
00:03:27,970 --> 00:03:29,670
 I like you. 

52
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:37,200
 It took me ten years to tell you that I like you. 

53
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:43,960
♫  As happy as I am, I am also sad  ♫

54
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:49,240
♫  I wish this dream would never end  ♫

55
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:54,000
What the heck? Are you already back?

56
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,170
Weren't you eating dinner?

57
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:10,750
Why did you buy so many beers? 
    

58
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,930
I don't know.

59
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:17,200
This is all because of Kim San Ha.

60
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:36,000
   

61
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,880
Today isn't the day you leave early.

62
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:44,800
What do you mean? There are days like this, too.

63
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:47,270
You've been acting strange since last night. Do you know that?

64
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:48,790
Have I?

65
00:04:49,820 --> 00:04:52,060
I'm going early since I have something to do.

66
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:54,780
Let's go. Let's go, let's go.

67
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:57,070
   

68
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:13,910
You're leaving early.

69
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,970
What the heck?

70
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:20,890
Hey, Yoon Joo Won. Why did you go back in?

71
00:05:20,890 --> 00:05:25,190
 I left something behind. You go ahead. 

72
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:31,670
Hello.

73
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:33,250
Hey.

74
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:44,340
Did anything happen with Joo Won yesterday?

75
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:46,190
“Yesterday”?

76
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:48,460
Something did happen.

77
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:50,890
She forgot about her date

78
00:05:50,890 --> 00:05:54,770
and came home with a bag of beers.

79
00:05:54,770 --> 00:05:56,180
I see.

80
00:05:57,830 --> 00:06:00,320
 This is all because of Kim San Ha. 

81
00:06:03,010 --> 00:06:05,250
Sunbae, you didn't let her go, did you?

82
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,700
Yes.

83
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:12,030
Why not? He seemed like a good person.

84
00:06:15,470 --> 00:06:17,120
Do you...

85
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,760
like Joo Won, by chance?

86
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,190
Really?

87
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:29,310
I heard you became an attorney.

88
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:33,440
Confidentiality is key for attorneys.

89
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:36,320
Yes, sure.

90
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:39,680
Okay.

91
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:46,120
 I like you. 

92
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,420
- Stop thinking about it. 
  - I like you. 

93
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:51,160
Stop thinking about it!

94
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,520
Who is it?

95
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,160
 It's me. 

96
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:07,970
Did you eat? Let's eat.

97
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,640
Sure.

98
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,780
What do you want to eat?

99
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:12,890
Do you eat toast and cereal? American style?

100
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:16,070
Or we can have rice if you want. I have side dishes.

101
00:07:16,070 --> 00:07:20,750
I always eat bread at the store, so Dad told me to eat rice at home.

102
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:23,290
There's beef broth and pickled perilla leaves.

103
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:25,380
I like it.

104
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:26,830
What?

105
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:30,050
I like it.

106
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,280
 I like you. 

107
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:35,890
 I like you. 

108
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:39,070
I really like pickled perilla leaves.

109
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:44,290
Why are you confessing to perilla leaves?

110
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:46,520
I'm just saying I like it. How else can I say it?

111
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,650
Eat what you want and go.

112
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:56,540
What is this?

113
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:58,500
You make us a quick meal because the children aren't here.

114
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,620
And you don't even have an appetite?

115
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:02,620
No, I just...

116
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:06,820
think I'm happy these days.

117
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,810
Is this how it feels to be full without eating?

118
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:13,750
What are you so happy about when they're on their own?

119
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:16,030
They're nearby, so we can see them every day.

120
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:19,890
And we can eat together whenever we want.

121
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:25,820
I'll take a look and buy good-quality beef if I see any.

122
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:27,730
Sounds good.

123
00:08:28,730 --> 00:08:30,940
Stop grinning and eat.

124
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:43,620
   

125
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:47,430
Hyungnim!

126
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,850
Yoon Joo Won didn't show up for the date. She stood him up.

127
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:52,820
I know.

128
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,400
You know?

129
00:08:55,530 --> 00:08:59,220
I have a hunch about why she did.

130
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:00,830
“A hunch”?

131
00:09:02,290 --> 00:09:05,730
I gave Joo Won flowers on her birthday.

132
00:09:05,730 --> 00:09:08,470
No wonder she really liked them.

133
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:12,090
I think she has really opened up to me since then.

134
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:16,280
Really? Do you think so?

135
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,090
Hyungnim.

136
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:21,360
Can you subtly ask Joo Won for me?

137
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,890
Why she didn't show up for the date.

138
00:09:23,890 --> 00:09:26,450
If it was because of the flowers,

139
00:09:26,450 --> 00:09:29,200
or because of me...

140
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:35,900
Whatever the reason, I don't think it was because of you.

141
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:39,130
Why not? Can't you just ask her for me?

142
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:11,320
Wait. I might've avoided him in the morning,

143
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:15,470
but how could he not contact me at all after shocking me like that?

144
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:18,740
Hello.

145
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,830
Welcome.

146
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,900
Madam.

147
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:34,370
Look who finally showed his face.

148
00:10:34,370 --> 00:10:37,840
Wow, are you taking rejuvenation medicine?

149
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,960
You look younger than you did 20 years ago.

150
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:42,140
You're teasing me.

151
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:46,250
Mr. Yoon, shower me with some salt.

152
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:48,250
Here.

153
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:57,930
Mr. Yoon, hurry up and marry Joo Won off.

154
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:59,370
What are you saying out of the blue?

155
00:10:59,370 --> 00:11:02,160
I went to a funeral today, and they only had one daughter.

156
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,530
So I worried for them.

157
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:09,440
And I noticed that she couldn't think straight after her father died,

158
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:13,940
so her husband took care of everything.

159
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:16,740
I'm still young, Madam.

160
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,210
Death doesn't follow an order.

161
00:11:18,210 --> 00:11:20,790
Do you think tickets are handed out?

162
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:23,630
Well, that's true, I guess.

163
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,940
Whatever. I'm not implying something grand.

164
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:31,420
It's better for you to have at least someone to lean on, right?

165
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:34,730
Well, I have Joo Won, San Ha, and Hae Joon.

166
00:11:34,730 --> 00:11:36,900
What is there to worry about?

167
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:39,240
He's not family.

168
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,280
Why am I not family?

169
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,410
We're father and son.

170
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,990
Right, right. “Son”?

171
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:46,040
Let's say you're his son.

172
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:49,590
Sons these days are absolutely useless.

173
00:11:49,590 --> 00:11:54,350
Once he gets married, his wife's family becomes his family.

174
00:11:54,350 --> 00:11:55,990
I won't get married, then.

175
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:58,110
Yes, right.

176
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,500
   

177
00:12:05,210 --> 00:12:07,170
Hello?

178
00:12:08,090 --> 00:12:10,280
Does he have people calling him up?

179
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:18,050
Madam, you have a tendency to look down on and tease Hae Joon.

180
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:22,050
Proof of family relations?

181
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:27,440
 Direct family relation must be confirmed for tax deductions to apply. 

182
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:31,020
All right. I'll call you back after looking into it.

183
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,290
Family relation...

184
00:13:20,730 --> 00:13:21,840
   

185
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:31,230
One, two, three.

186
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,770
What's up?

187
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:35,920
 Did you eat? 

188
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,940
Yes, I did.

189
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:46,430
Hello?

190
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:48,720
 Aren't you going to ask me? 

191
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:52,050
Look at the time.

192
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:53,840
You probably already ate.

193
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:57,570
 You still always asked if I'd eaten. 

194
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:01,280
 And you'd tell me to eat if I hadn't. 

195
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:03,920
 Or ask me what I ate if I had. 

196
00:14:06,770 --> 00:14:10,880
Ahjusshi wants you to come to eat tomorrow.

197
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:14,600
No. I'll go separately.

198
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:18,650
I need to do market research tomorrow. Yes.

199
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:21,050
- I'll see you tomorrow. 
 - Joo–

200
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:23,850
   

201
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,820
Do you want me to go with you?

202
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:35,840
You said you're doing market research in the morning.

203
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:43,770
I'm just going to look around.

204
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:45,370
It's okay.

205
00:14:49,010 --> 00:14:50,710
Who was that on the phone?

206
00:14:50,710 --> 00:14:52,670
Kim San Ha.

207
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:55,800
Really?

208
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,280
But why were you so awkward?

209
00:14:59,110 --> 00:15:01,420
Did something happen with Sunbae and you?

210
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:03,180
 I like you. 

211
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:07,790
 It took me ten years to tell you that I like you. 

212
00:15:08,570 --> 00:15:10,370
Was it obvious?

213
00:15:10,370 --> 00:15:13,020
Yes, very.

214
00:15:14,780 --> 00:15:18,980
I have clients who claim they don't know anything,

215
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:21,570
but I can tell they're lying right away.

216
00:15:21,570 --> 00:15:26,430
You just sounded exactly like them.

217
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:29,400
 You're not oblivious. 

218
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:32,680
 You know what I'm trying to tell you. 

219
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,360
I don't know what I should do.

220
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:40,930
I don't know.

221
00:16:02,270 --> 00:16:04,720
What about the store you looked into?

222
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:07,440
Just tell Ahjusshi about it.

223
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:10,540
It's fine. I found a way.

224
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:12,680
What way?

225
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,840
Give me a heads-up if you'll do something stupid.

226
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,420
You just worry about yourself.

227
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:19,040
You still have something to tell Ahjusshi, too.

228
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,620
I'll take care of myself.

229
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:22,990
You escalate small matters.

230
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:26,200
Your fiery mouth is still the same.

231
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:29,560
I'm telling you not to make any trouble.

232
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:31,340
When did I ever make trouble?

233
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:33,630
Don't you remember when Joo Won fell into the pond?

234
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:36,200
You call yourself an oppa, yet you called her crazy?

235
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,660
My goodness, that was ages ago.

236
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,630
Oppas!

237
00:16:39,630 --> 00:16:42,430
Where did you come from?

238
00:16:42,430 --> 00:16:43,810
I was waiting for you guys.

239
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:45,440
Let's go eat meat.

240
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,770
It's been forever since I had meat. Delicious.

241
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:49,850
I heard it's Korean beef today.

242
00:16:49,850 --> 00:16:53,520
Korean beef. Meat.

243
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,770
Meat.

244
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:01,240
Meat.

245
00:17:02,530 --> 00:17:04,650
Meat.

246
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:09,170
Oppa. Pass me the salt.

247
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:10,890
What? Me?

248
00:17:10,890 --> 00:17:12,410
Yes.

249
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:14,660
Sure, sure.

250
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:17,680
Oppa, pass me the onion.

251
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:33,680
How did you live without calling them Oppa all this time?

252
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:36,340
Exactly. I'll say it all at once to make up for it.

253
00:17:36,340 --> 00:17:39,190
I should call them a lot so I can adjust quickly.

254
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:08,580
I have something to say.

255
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:12,100
- What is it? 
 - What is it?

256
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,540
Let's...

257
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,740
get married.

258
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:41,110
Why not?

259
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:43,650
It's not like it's out of the question.

260
00:18:43,650 --> 00:18:45,140
Didn't you also say back then?

261
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:48,910
That we can't inherit anything, and it's useless even if we win the lottery.

262
00:18:48,910 --> 00:18:51,840
Dad and Ahjusshi won’t go through a complicated adoption process.

263
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:55,540
All of that is possible if you and I get married.

264
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:01,930
We don't need to inherit the one store Mr. Yoon owns.

265
00:19:01,930 --> 00:19:05,970
And I don't even dream about empty hope like winning the lottery anymore.

266
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:08,470
If you want to legally become family,

267
00:19:08,470 --> 00:19:11,700
how about one of you think about adoption?

268
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:15,210
No. Not his son.

269
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:17,670
Madam said a son-in-law is better than a son.

270
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:19,000
Darn it.

271
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,100
Tell Dad to adopt a daughter if you want to become his son-in-law.

272
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:24,810
- Why do you keep involving me? 
 - That's enough.

