That's love.

539
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:41,090
You honestly agree with me, right?

540
00:39:41,090 --> 00:39:42,890
I do.

541
00:39:42,890 --> 00:39:45,530
- Mr. Yoon Jeong Jae. 
 - Yes.

542
00:39:47,750 --> 00:39:49,360
Okay...

543
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,110
Does it feel tingly, too?

544
00:39:51,110 --> 00:39:53,060
Yes, a little.

545
00:39:53,060 --> 00:39:54,990
What about the other leg?

546
00:39:54,990 --> 00:39:58,000
That leg also feels tingly sometimes, right?

547
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:01,160
It does happen at night, but it's not severe.

548
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:03,460
It doesn't seem to simply be muscle pain.

549
00:40:03,460 --> 00:40:05,950
Let's take an x-ray.

550
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:10,870
   

551
00:40:21,350 --> 00:40:22,510
   

552
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:28,390
I was not in my right mind last time.

553
00:40:28,390 --> 00:40:31,060
I shouldn't have taken it out on you, Doctor.

554
00:40:31,060 --> 00:40:34,660
It's just that when you said my dad might not walk again,

555
00:40:34,660 --> 00:40:40,020
I was worried he might really never get to walk again.

556
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:44,830
I was too overwhelmed about what to do.

557
00:40:44,830 --> 00:40:50,800
I also felt guilty having those thoughts.

558
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:55,600
At first...

559
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:59,250
you don't know why this is happening to you.

560
00:40:59,250 --> 00:41:01,830
You'll get angry and frustrated.

561
00:41:03,310 --> 00:41:05,700
You'll be tormented.

562
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:09,300
But he's still alive.

563
00:41:11,330 --> 00:41:15,210
I think that's more than enough.

564
00:41:16,010 --> 00:41:18,880
Because that's what you were most desperate for.

565
00:41:23,580 --> 00:41:25,270
Everything will be okay.

566
00:41:25,270 --> 00:41:27,160
Thank you.

567
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,930
You're really a doctor.

568
00:41:47,930 --> 00:41:49,790
I graduated medical school at the top of my class.

569
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:53,120
Does medical school teach how to empathize, too?

570
00:41:53,120 --> 00:41:55,480
Were you also at the top of the class for that?

571
00:42:07,350 --> 00:42:08,950
Your hand.

572
00:42:13,750 --> 00:42:16,120
No, your left hand.

573
00:42:18,490 --> 00:42:22,640
♫  I keep rattling  ♫

574
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:29,380
♫  Like a broken doll  ♫

575
00:42:30,350 --> 00:42:34,980
♫  I'm lost on every step  ♫

576
00:42:38,070 --> 00:42:41,440
How did you know my left wrist was hurting?

577
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:44,970
It's obvious if you care.

578
00:42:44,970 --> 00:42:49,480
♫  My day is spent immersed in a dream  ♫

579
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:51,470
I'll begin.

580
00:42:53,810 --> 00:42:57,070
♫  I have a lot to say  ♫

581
00:42:57,070 --> 00:43:00,400
Is it okay? It's not too hot, right?

582
00:43:02,820 --> 00:43:04,730
How is it?

583
00:43:04,730 --> 00:43:06,630
Is it bearable?

584
00:43:08,230 --> 00:43:14,100
♫  Why am I like this?  ♫

585
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:22,290
♫  Why am I always so excited like it's the first time?  ♫

586
00:43:22,290 --> 00:43:26,190
♫  And remorseful like it's the last time?  ♫

587
00:43:26,190 --> 00:43:27,900
Are you okay?

588
00:43:27,900 --> 00:43:31,820
♫  Again, I circle around you like I'm praying  ♫

589
00:43:31,820 --> 00:43:35,400
♫  When our eyes meet  ♫

590
00:43:35,400 --> 00:43:37,820
This feels nice because it's warm.

591
00:43:37,820 --> 00:43:42,630
♫  When you look at me  ♫

592
00:43:42,630 --> 00:43:45,750
♫  The freezing winter melts  ♫

593
00:43:45,750 --> 00:43:51,470
♫  Even in the dark night, the sun shines  ♫

594
00:43:51,470 --> 00:43:55,430
♫  Do you know what this means?  ♫

595
00:43:55,430 --> 00:43:59,950
The nurse will come later and wrap it up for you.

596
00:44:01,750 --> 00:44:03,190
Why did you have to whisper that?

597
00:44:03,190 --> 00:44:04,280
No reason.

598
00:44:04,280 --> 00:44:06,040
Stay here for a minute.

599
00:44:29,370 --> 00:44:32,640
Yes. Is Dad okay?

600
00:44:33,470 --> 00:44:36,630
I'm glad. Okay, I'll be in the lobby.

601
00:44:39,990 --> 00:44:44,300
Hey, does Kang Hae Joon have a girlfriend or not?

602
00:44:45,380 --> 00:44:47,170
He doesn't have a girlfriend.

603
00:44:47,170 --> 00:44:48,850
He doesn't?

604
00:44:49,630 --> 00:44:51,620
But I think there's a woman he wants to marry.

605
00:44:51,620 --> 00:44:53,280
“Marry”? Who is it?

606
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:54,950
What does she do? Did they date for long?

607
00:44:54,950 --> 00:44:57,000
You said you lived together. You must know.

608
00:44:57,000 --> 00:44:58,530
Gosh, I really don't know.

609
00:44:58,530 --> 00:44:59,840
Hey, you've seen her, haven't you?

610
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:02,280
- You have. Is she pretty? 
 - I haven't.

611
00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:04,660
- Hey, aren't you being too mean? 
 - What?

612
00:45:04,660 --> 00:45:06,480
I mean...

613
00:45:17,670 --> 00:45:19,800
Why do you look so happy?

614
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:23,360
Those two look so great together.

615
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:26,810
I think San Ha will be the first one to get married.

616
00:45:28,630 --> 00:45:32,610
Yes, once you start getting married, one by one,

617
00:45:32,610 --> 00:45:37,270
I'll see my grandchildren and become a grandpa in no time.

618
00:45:37,270 --> 00:45:39,850
Are you happy about becoming a grandpa?

619
00:45:41,770 --> 00:45:44,490
- I don't know. 
 - Come on, tell me.

620
00:45:44,490 --> 00:45:47,100
Later. Ahjusshi.

621
00:45:50,500 --> 00:45:51,770
Are you all done?

622
00:45:51,770 --> 00:45:54,270
My back feels better already.

623
00:45:54,270 --> 00:45:58,360
Just a few more treatments, and you'll be okay.

624
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:01,290
Yes, thanks to you, San Ha.

625
00:46:01,290 --> 00:46:06,060
By the way, who's the doctor who greeted me?

626
00:46:06,060 --> 00:46:07,580
You two seem very close.

627
00:46:07,580 --> 00:46:10,690
Oh, it's not like that. We are high school friends.

628
00:46:10,690 --> 00:46:12,650
She's also my college alumni.

629
00:46:12,650 --> 00:46:14,750
Oh, Joo Won, you know Hui Joo, too, right?

630
00:46:14,750 --> 00:46:16,060
I do know her.

631
00:46:16,060 --> 00:46:20,610
Really? You even work together. That's no ordinary connection.

632
00:46:20,610 --> 00:46:22,570
Of course. That's no ordinary connection.

633
00:46:22,570 --> 00:46:24,050
She used to date Kang Hae Joon.

634
00:46:24,050 --> 00:46:26,260
I see...

635
00:46:26,260 --> 00:46:27,810
What? “Date Hae Joon”?

636
00:46:27,810 --> 00:46:30,880
She dumped Kang Hae Joon and failed to secure a rebound relationship.

637
00:46:30,880 --> 00:46:33,430
Is that so? With whom?

638
00:46:33,430 --> 00:46:36,370
I don't know. I wonder who?

639
00:46:44,940 --> 00:46:47,160
Oh my gosh!

640
00:46:48,260 --> 00:46:49,840
Are you home?

641
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:51,990
What are you doing over there?

642
00:46:56,950 --> 00:46:59,110
Did you sleep here?

643
00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:08,100
Is Ahjusshi's condition that bad?

644
00:47:08,100 --> 00:47:11,650
No, he's fine.

645
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:14,350
That's good to hear.

646
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:19,050
   

647
00:47:19,050 --> 00:47:21,680
My mom is back at it again.

648
00:47:21,680 --> 00:47:24,740
“Again”? A blind date?

649
00:47:24,740 --> 00:47:28,220
Yes, another blind date.

650
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:33,620
Mom knows I'm no good with strangers.

651
00:47:34,420 --> 00:47:36,720
As soon as I sit down, it's like getting interviewed.

652
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:40,480
We ask about hobbies, specialties, salaries, and retirement plans.

653
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:44,250
How does she expect my heart to flutter for someone like that?

654
00:47:45,010 --> 00:47:46,790
Heart-fluttering?

655
00:47:48,700 --> 00:47:51,090
 It's obvious if you care. 

656
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:53,880
Heart-fluttering?

657
00:47:57,050 --> 00:48:01,140
Heart-fluttering. That's the problem.

658
00:48:01,140 --> 00:48:03,300
Why is that a problem?

659
00:48:05,470 --> 00:48:08,280
Someone must've made your heart flutter recently.

660
00:48:09,130 --> 00:48:11,070
And if they did?

661
00:48:11,070 --> 00:48:13,310
Is that such a big deal?

662
00:48:14,010 --> 00:48:15,960
My heart flutters when I bake perfect cake sheets,

663
00:48:15,960 --> 00:48:18,290
and when a first-time customer says my cake is delicious.

664
00:48:18,290 --> 00:48:20,810
My heart is a-always fluttering.

665
00:48:21,610 --> 00:48:23,920
Do you call that heart-fluttering?

666
00:48:26,470 --> 00:48:29,870
Did you know? After my clients'

667
00:48:29,870 --> 00:48:34,860
“I didn't know anything” phase, the next phase is,

668
00:48:34,860 --> 00:48:37,380
"I must've misunderstood!"

669
00:48:37,380 --> 00:48:38,960
It's that.

670
00:48:39,820 --> 00:48:41,530
“Misunderstood”?

671
00:48:42,970 --> 00:48:45,410
You're right. I must've misunderstood.

672
00:48:45,410 --> 00:48:48,060
You're right. I misunderstood. That's it.

673
00:48:51,450 --> 00:48:55,810
How long must I ignore when she's being that obvious?

674
00:48:55,810 --> 00:48:57,430
Of course.

675
00:48:57,430 --> 00:48:58,910
Is heart-fluttering such a big deal?

676
00:48:58,910 --> 00:49:00,710
It could be out of worry for Kim San Ha.

677
00:49:00,710 --> 00:49:03,770
It could flutter because...

678
00:49:03,770 --> 00:49:07,670
he's fine, thanks to me.

679
00:49:07,670 --> 00:49:11,740
That's all heart-warming. My heart flutters because it's all heart-warming.

680
00:49:11,740 --> 00:49:13,950
Familial love. It's just familial love.

681
00:49:13,950 --> 00:49:17,070
I shouldn't misunderstand that for heart-fluttering.

682
00:49:17,980 --> 00:49:19,420
Yes.

683
00:49:21,030 --> 00:49:22,930
 When do you close from work tomorrow? 

684
00:49:22,930 --> 00:49:24,860
 Do you want to grab dinner? 

685
00:49:30,850 --> 00:49:36,750
 This is the place where most of the electricity we use is generated 

686
00:49:36,750 --> 00:49:39,680
from hydropower and nuclear power.

687
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:43,730
This yellow ball you see here is called Uranium.

688
00:49:43,730 --> 00:49:49,860
Generating electricity with this uranium is called nuclear energy.

689
00:49:49,860 --> 00:49:52,360
Isn't that dangerous if there's an earthquake?

690
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:55,220
You might be worried about it collapsing if there's an earthquake,

691
00:49:55,220 --> 00:49:57,910
like our friend over there.

692
00:49:57,910 --> 00:50:01,400
That's why it's designed to be earthquake-resistant.

693
00:50:01,400 --> 00:50:03,680
Earthquake-resistant design is building structures

694
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:06,810
to withstand or absorb the earthquake shock.

695
00:50:06,810 --> 00:50:11,720
They make it this safe, so there's no reason for our friends to get worried, right?

696
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:13,520
 Yes. 

697
00:50:13,520 --> 00:50:14,960
See you next time.

698
00:50:14,960 --> 00:50:17,150
 - Goodbye.  
 - Goodbye!

699
00:50:17,150 --> 00:50:19,340
Please follow me.

700
00:50:19,340 --> 00:50:22,780
Hold your partner's hand.

701
00:50:22,780 --> 00:50:24,420
Auntie.

702
00:50:39,100 --> 00:50:42,170
Are you really Hae Joon?

703
00:50:42,170 --> 00:50:44,560
How are you exactly the same?

704
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:46,310
You've become cooler.

705
00:50:46,310 --> 00:50:49,000
How are you so good at those explanations?

706
00:50:51,670 --> 00:50:56,100
Let's go. I'll buy you something delicious.

707
00:51:10,340 --> 00:51:11,640
You should eat, too.

708
00:51:11,640 --> 00:51:13,380
One might think I'm acting like a child.

709
00:51:13,380 --> 00:51:15,400
Should I order you another one?

710
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:16,720
I'll finish this first.

711
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:19,400
Why? Eat one more.

712
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:24,850
Didn't you always say bulgogi burgers were the tastiest in the world?

713
00:51:27,270 --> 00:51:29,960
They don't have bulgogi burgers in America.

714
00:51:29,960 --> 00:51:34,650
That really stuck in my head when you went to America.

715
00:51:47,560 --> 00:51:48,970
Auntie.

716
00:51:50,020 --> 00:51:51,510
Yes.

717
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:55,000
What?

718
00:51:59,850 --> 00:52:02,110
Never mind. Get going.

719
00:52:02,110 --> 00:52:03,740
I'm leaving.

720
00:52:06,830 --> 00:52:09,100
She hasn't contacted you, right?

721
00:52:13,420 --> 00:52:15,860
I was just wondering.

722
00:52:18,720 --> 00:52:21,470
I got a new phone number, so not many people know it.

723
00:52:21,470 --> 00:52:23,470
There is no one to contact me.

724
00:52:25,390 --> 00:52:26,960
Take care.

725
00:52:27,990 --> 00:52:30,400
- I'll get going, then. 
 - Okay.

726
00:52:58,930 --> 00:53:02,290
Why did Auntie have to bring up Mom?

727
00:53:33,300 --> 00:53:35,210
Of course. Of course.

728
00:53:35,210 --> 00:53:37,940
It ended early today since I just got prescriptions.

729
00:53:37,940 --> 00:53:40,800
Yes, and I bought everything I needed to.

730
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:44,800
I have to get going to prepare for dinner hours.

731
00:53:44,800 --> 00:53:48,510
Yes, I'll call you back. It's nothing.

732
00:53:48,510 --> 00:53:51,300
- Aigoo, it's fine. 
 - I'm sorry.

733
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:52,610
There's nothing that can shatter.

734
00:53:52,610 --> 00:53:53,790
- But still. 
 - Yes, yes. I'm sorry.

735
00:53:53,790 --> 00:53:55,840
Gosh, I'm sorry.

736
00:54:31,780 --> 00:54:33,640
Why are you here?

737
00:54:34,850 --> 00:54:36,900
I...

738
00:54:36,900 --> 00:54:38,460
What?

739
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:42,740
What is it?

740
00:54:45,780 --> 00:54:47,870
It's nothing.

741
00:54:52,430 --> 00:54:54,720
Will you tell Joo Won?

742
00:54:54,720 --> 00:54:56,980
I have no intention of telling her.

743
00:54:56,980 --> 00:54:58,470
Don't you remember?

744
00:54:58,470 --> 00:55:01,030
I didn't tell her back then, either.

745
00:55:03,130 --> 00:55:06,250
That's right. You didn't.

746
00:55:09,390 --> 00:55:13,580
But this time, it'll come with a price.

747
00:55:14,320 --> 00:55:16,520
What price?

748
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:18,470
Can you...

749
00:55:19,970 --> 00:55:22,380
be my boyfriend?

750
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:37,520
You could just ask me to ruin your blind date.

751
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:40,480
You surprised me when you asked me to be your boyfriend.

752
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:47,370
Well, you are my boyfriend for a day.

753
00:55:48,490 --> 00:55:50,820
But is that really necessary?

754
00:55:50,820 --> 00:55:55,640
You can just tell him, "Sorry, but I don't think we are suited for each other."

755
00:55:55,640 --> 00:55:58,640
I tried that a couple of times.

756
00:55:58,640 --> 00:56:02,900
- “A couple of times”? 
 - But Mom keeps arranging another date.

757
00:56:06,590 --> 00:56:11,000
So will you help me or not?

758
00:56:13,630 --> 00:56:16,360
What kind of boyfriend do you want?

759
00:56:23,480 --> 00:56:25,570
Yi Yeon told me...

760
00:56:26,290 --> 00:56:29,940
Hae Joon came back to Korea.

761
00:56:31,540 --> 00:56:34,300
Did you keep in touch with your younger sister?

762
00:56:34,300 --> 00:56:36,050
No.

763
00:56:36,050 --> 00:56:38,300
I didn't.

764
00:56:38,300 --> 00:56:42,170
She contacted me recently after a long time.

765
00:56:42,170 --> 00:56:45,200
She said I should at least be aware.

766
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:53,070
Let's not delay and call Hae Joon over here.

767
00:56:53,070 --> 00:56:54,800
No.

768
00:56:56,610 --> 00:56:58,750
I didn't come to meet him.

769
00:56:58,750 --> 00:57:03,310
I just came to get a glimpse of his face.

770
00:57:04,500 --> 00:57:08,440
You must've come all the way here because you miss Hae Joon.

771
00:57:09,240 --> 00:57:12,520
No. It's not like that.

772
00:57:18,460 --> 00:57:22,260
Did you know Hae Joon injured his leg in America?

773
00:57:22,260 --> 00:57:25,150
- Pardon? 
 - That's why he quit basketball.

774
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:31,430
Can you imagine how much he must've suffered alone in that far and foreign country?

775
00:57:34,140 --> 00:57:35,790
Sure.

776
00:57:37,510 --> 00:57:39,050
See him before you go.

777
00:57:39,050 --> 00:57:41,980
It's not a hard request.

778
00:57:41,980 --> 00:57:45,970
No, please just pretend you never saw me today.

779
00:57:45,970 --> 00:57:49,200
Hey, wait. Wait a minute.

780
00:57:52,500 --> 00:57:55,600
Are you scared Hae Joon will be angry at you? He won't.

781
00:57:55,600 --> 00:57:59,540
He will forget you never called him all this time with just one hug from you.

782
00:57:59,540 --> 00:58:02,370
How can you not know your own son?

783
00:58:04,240 --> 00:58:06,390
It doesn't matter.

784
00:58:13,370 --> 00:58:14,560
How could you be so coldhearted?

785
00:58:14,560 --> 00:58:16,510
Don't follow me. I said I wouldn't see him.

786
00:58:16,510 --> 00:58:18,000
No.

787
00:58:18,710 --> 00:58:20,140
I can't do that.

788
00:58:20,140 --> 00:58:22,800
I deeply regretted it ten years ago, too.

789
00:58:22,800 --> 00:58:27,490
If I had held onto you then, Hae Joon could've seen his mom's face at least once.

790
00:58:30,890 --> 00:58:33,210
- I... 
 - Yes?

791
00:58:34,500 --> 00:58:36,990
I killed someone.

792
00:58:41,710 --> 00:58:44,330
I killed someone.

793
00:58:56,450 --> 00:58:57,970
Is this really enough?

794
00:58:57,970 --> 00:59:00,700
This place is really good.

795
00:59:04,480 --> 00:59:06,050
Good as always.

796
00:59:06,050 --> 00:59:08,480
I told you I'd buy you something delicious.

797
00:59:10,970 --> 00:59:14,870
I must be really happy these days.

798
00:59:14,870 --> 00:59:20,190
My life was good and uneventful even without Hae Joon and you,

799
00:59:20,190 --> 00:59:26,790
but I'm a lot happier now that you guys are back.

800
00:59:29,200 --> 00:59:33,170
It feels like we are back in high school when the three of us were together.

